    <item>
      <title>Model Train Collecting</title>
      <link>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/model-train-collecting/</link>
      <comments>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/model-train-collecting/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 02 Apr 2011 23:12:01 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Trains O Scale</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Trains O Scale]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Model Train Collecting]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://trainsoscaledepot.com/?p=4292</guid>
      <description>Hello, my name is Mark… The model train hobby is what I consider to be one of the best hobbies in the world. On this page, I’ll give you some of my background and recommend some fantastic model train resources that will teach you the best way to become involved in trains O scale as [...]&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/model-train-collecting/"&gt;Model Train Collecting&lt;/a&gt; is a post from: &lt;a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com"&gt;Trains O Scale&lt;/a&gt;:blog where you can get news on Trains O Scale and other model train collecting news.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/trains-o-scale/Trains_O_Scale-Model_Train_Collecting.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="attachment_4288" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/elsie/165602383/in/set-72157594163437997/"><img class="size-medium wp-image-4288" title="O gauge model railway at Kew Bridge museum" src="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/800px-O_gauge_at_Kew-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">source: http://www.flickr.com/photos/elsie/165602383/in/set-72157594163437997/</p></div>
<h3><strong> Hello, my name is Mark… </strong></h3>
<p>The model train hobby is what I consider to be one of the best hobbies in the world. On this page, I’ll  give you some of my background and recommend some fantastic model train resources that will teach you the  best way to become involved in <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/home/" >trains O scale</a> as well as HO, N, and G  scale modeling that covers detailed information for a complete beginner  as well as for very advanced levels.</p>
<p>I was first exposed to this amazing hobby when I was  just 7 years of  age. I was in awe of my uncle&#8217;s O scale model train set and still remember fondly the days  when he would be building scenes and displays and operating the trains  while letting me watch and assist.</p>
<p>Ever since that time, I had wanted to build my own, slowly but  surely, as finances would allow and birthdays would come. New tracks,  locomotives, passenger carriages, scene and display kits and anything  else I could get my hands on.  To this day, I prefer the O scale train  sets due to their larger size, various scales, large amount of  accessories and very detailed design. I remember spending so much time  in several hobby shops admiring the large range of different accessories  and desiring to add certain items to my display.</p>
<p>Now, as an adult, I enjoy it even more and do not believe this is  something you grow out of. What is unique about model train collecting  is that is can be a hobby for life, enjoyed simultaneously by different  generations!  It is so enjoyable to be creative and and to develop more  intimate knowledge of geography from making landscapes. Taking various  ideas and morphing them into life like miniatures makes me feel like I  am going back in time and entering another world.</p>
<p>There is no doubt, due to the complexity of this hobby, that model  train collecting can certainly come with its frustrations. There are SO  many various books and manuals, few of which have everything you need.  Most just seem to focus on a specific area.</p>
<h3><strong>The major issue with model train collecting<br />
</strong></h3>
<p>With all the latest advancements in model train collecting, it is  very easy to make some expensive mistakes.</p>
<p>For this reason, I decided to review the model train “how to” books  on the market…</p>
<p>For the most part, they were just adequate. Beginners, or advanced  railroaders, would have to buy many books/manuals just to get 80% of the  information they needed. This was the case until I found 2 downloadable  ebooks –<a href="http://www.trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner"> </a><a href="http://www.trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank"><strong><em>Model Trains for Beginners</em></strong></a> and <em><strong><a rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/modeltrainhelp" target="_blank">Model Train Help</a></strong>.</em></p>
<p>These two books have become my only source of information!</p>
<p>Further, since they are ebooks, the authors update them often and  will give you the updates free of charge. I can’t tell you how many  books I’ve got on my shelf with very outdated information… a problem  easily solved with these ebooks.</p>
<p>Both the authors also offer a 60 day money back guarantee… so if the  ebook doesn’t suit your needs you can request a full refund…</p>
<h3><strong>Here’s an Overview of Both…</strong></h3>
<p><strong><a rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-147" title="Model Trains for Beginners" src="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/package-tight.jpg" alt="" width="318" height="366" /></a><br />
</strong></p>
<p><strong> 1) <a rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank">Model Trains for Beginners</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><a title="click here to review Model Trains for Beginners" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/wazak.hobbyshop.hop.clickbank.net/?tid=BLOGRECOMMENDED');" rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank">Model Trains for Beginners</a> – is my # 1 choice.</strong> This is a “must have” ebook for all beginners to <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/home/" >trains o scale</a> and all other scales and concepts regarding model train collecting.</p>
<p>It is full of rock-solid and high quality information  for those beginning their model train collecting.</p>
<p>Even modelers with vast experience will gain much insight as there is an unbelievable amount of useful  information in this ebook . It always helps to have something that brings you back to all of the basics and can provide a reference for use on a daily basis.</p>
<p>In spite of all the research I have done,   I still found more than a few tips in <strong><a rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank">Model Trains for Beginners</a></strong> that could have saved  me hundreds of dollars had I been aware of them before. Further, this information is for all scales, not just <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-o-scale/home/" >trains O scale</a> model trains.</p>
<p>It covers the essential basics from the  ground up including the language of model trains, how to conceptualize your plan, and the design and creation of fantastic layouts that are easy to run and problem free. You will also get exposure to advanced realism techniques like weathering, how to make your layout look  dated, as well as controllers and tips for those people who are not  Electricians, and so much more.</p>
<p>This is a very well priced ebook at $47, as you  would not normally find this amount of condensed, straight to the point  information in one book, and comes with $135 of free bonuses. Again, it would be necessary to purchase 5 or 6 books to get the  equivalent amount of information.</p>
<p>It also comes with 7 bonuses that make the  investment well worth it.</p>
<p>&gt;&gt;<a href="http://www.trainsoscaledepot.com/beginner" target="_blank"> <strong>To get more  information on “Model Trains for Beginners” – Click here</strong></a></p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/modeltrainhelp.html"></a><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/modeltrainhelp"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-154" title="Model Train Help" src="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/affiliatesebookcover.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="346" /></a><strong>2) <a rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/modeltrainhelp" target="_blank">Model Train Help</a></strong></p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/modeltrainhelp" target="_blank"><strong>Model  Train Help</strong></a> is the perfect resource for intermediate  to advanced model railroaders.</p>
<p>It is a detailed 200+ page ebook packed with detailed technical solutions. While beginners will find  this ebook overwhelming, the intermediate to advanced model railroader  will find the information incredibly useful. You will gain exposure to  everything from  the language of model trains, to complete details regarding planning, designing and creating great  layouts that are easy to run and problem free, to weathering and so much  more… this ebook has it all.</p>
<p>It is US$39.97, but you would need 5 or 6  books from <strong>Amazon</strong> to give you all the  condensed information this ebook contains in one place.</p>
<p>&gt;&gt;   <strong><a title="Model Train  Help" rel="nofollow" href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/modeltrainhelp" target="_blank">To get more  information on “Model Train Help” – Click here</a></strong></p>
<p><strong><br />
</strong></p>
