      <title>Model Train Secrets Exposed</title>
      <link>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/recommended-resources/recommended-resource-model-train-secrets-exposed/</link>
      <comments>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/recommended-resources/recommended-resource-model-train-secrets-exposed/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 May 2010 18:17:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Trains O Scale</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Recommended Resources]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Electric Train Sets]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Model Train Collecting]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Model Train Layout]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[o scale trains]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Trains O Scale]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://trainsoscaledepot.com/?p=225</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[The hobby of model train collecting can be initially overwhelming to someone just wanting to get started. With all the variables included, such as the wiring, benchwork, tracks, different types of scales of locomotives, and scenery, model train collecting can be downright complex. There is certainly much to absorb when taking on this hobby in [...]<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/recommended-resources/recommended-resource-model-train-secrets-exposed/">Model Train Secrets Exposed</a> is a post from: <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com">Trains O Scale</a>:blog where you can get news on Trains O Scale and other model train collecting news.</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/secrets"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-227" title="Modeltrainsecrets" src="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/Modeltrainsecrets.jpg" alt="" width="221" height="315" /></a>The hobby of model train collecting can be initially overwhelming to someone just wanting to get started. With all the variables included, such as the wiring, benchwork, tracks, different types of scales of locomotives, and scenery, model train collecting can be downright complex. There is certainly much to absorb when taking on this hobby in addition to the fact that it can be quite expensive.</p>
<p>For example, the cost of a model locomotive with a decoder (Digital command Control) can be in the hundreds of dollars! Add that to the added cost of accessories such as rolling stocks, model train tracks, scenery, buildings, lighting, power packs and more. However, getting involved can be much easier than one would think with the proper guidance.</p>
<p>Thus, in order to avoid all the common mistakes made by new railroaders and potentially wasting a great deal of time and expense, I highly recommend <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/secrets" target="_blank">&#8220;Model Trains Secrets Exposed: The Ultimate Guide for Beginners&#8221;</a> by Gerald Delaney an absolute must for anyone considering this hobby.</p>
<p>You will learn the following:</p>
<p>1. Setting up your train quickly and easily</p>
<p>2. Getting the scale and gauge for your needs</p>
<p>3. Getting your layout as beautiful as possible &#8212; within your budget</p>
<p>4. Preventing derailments and damage to your trains</p>
<p>5. Having fun with the hobby</p>
<p>This system is so effective because it&#8217;s based on getting and KEEPING your track conditions just right.</p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/secrets" target="_blank">&#8220;Model Trains Secrets Exposed: The Ultimate Guide for Beginners&#8221;</a></p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/recommended-resources/recommended-resource-model-train-secrets-exposed/">Model Train Secrets Exposed</a> is a post from: <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com">Trains O Scale</a>:blog where you can get news on Trains O Scale and other model train collecting news.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/recommended-resources/recommended-resource-model-train-secrets-exposed/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Electric Train HO Scale – The Most Popular Choice</title>
      <link>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/ho-scale/electric-train-ho/</link>
      <comments>http://trainsoscaledepot.com/ho-scale/electric-train-ho/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sat, 22 May 2010 21:48:55 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Trains O Scale</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[HO scale]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[electric train ho]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://trainsoscaledepot.com/?p=77</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Image via Wikipedia Currently, electric train ho scales are the most popular of all the railroad scales in both the USA and Europe. When interest in model train collecting started diminishing around the 1950&#8242;s,  hobbyists began to demand more realism in their pastime, hence the beginning of the scale popularity. With electric train ho scale [...]<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/ho-scale/electric-train-ho/">Electric Train HO Scale &#8211; The Most Popular Choice</a> is a post from: <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com">Trains O Scale</a>:blog where you can get news on Trains O Scale and other model train collecting news.</p>
]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="zemanta-img" style="margin: 1em; display: block;">
<div>
<dl class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 310px;">
<dt class="wp-caption-dt"><a href="http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:ArsTECNICA_Anlage1.jpg"><img title="Model train HO - Modélisme de train HO" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/ArsTECNICA_Anlage1.jpg/300px-ArsTECNICA_Anlage1.jpg" alt="Model train HO - Modélisme de train HO" width="300" height="188" /></a></dt>
<dd class="wp-caption-dd zemanta-img-attribution" style="font-size: 0.8em;">Image via <a href="http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:ArsTECNICA_Anlage1.jpg">Wikipedia</a></dd>
</dl>
</div>
</div>
<p>Currently, <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-ho-scale/electric-train-ho/" >electric train ho scales</a> are the most popular of all the railroad scales in both the USA and Europe. When interest in model train collecting started diminishing around the 1950&#8242;s,  hobbyists began to demand more realism in their pastime, hence the beginning of the scale popularity. With electric train ho scale trains, model train hobbyists are able to fit in more details into a comparable area than that of the O scale. The resulting displays possess a great deal more realism than that of many other scales.</p>
<p>As a result of the great popularity of <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-ho-scale/electric-train-ho/" >electric train ho scales</a>, locomotives and many accessories such as scenery, cars, carriages, and buildings are readily available and can be located through a large number of manufacturers.</p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-ho-scale/electric-train-ho/" >Electric train ho scales</a> are generally available in three options:</p>
<p>1) <strong>Ready-to-Run</strong> &#8211; Options that are completely ready for use right out of the box.</p>
<p>2) <strong>Shake the Box</strong> &#8211; Kits that are easy to assemble. For example, a freight car might include a one-piece body, a  chassis, trucks, couplers, and a counterweight, while a structure kit  might include walls, windows, doors, and glazing.</p>
<p>3)<strong> </strong><strong>Craftsman Kits</strong> &#8211; Kits that require a much higher level of skill to assemble  and can include several hundreds of parts and accessories.</p>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/trains-ho-scale/electric-train-ho/" >Electric train ho scales</a> are the most popular scale for many reasons. First, as previously mentioned, it is large enough for a great amount of detail, much more so than the  smaller scales but, large enough to be handled by children. They are usually less expensive than all the other scales and allow elaborate track displays in a smaller space. Thus, essentially, the electric train ho scale sets provide the perfect balance between the detail of the larger G, O and S scale sets and the lower space required for the smaller N and Z scales.</p>
<div class="zemanta-pixie" style="margin-top: 10px; height: 15px;"><a class="zemanta-pixie-a" title="Enhanced by Zemanta" href="http://www.zemanta.com/"><img class="zemanta-pixie-img" style="border: medium none; float: right;" src="http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=1ce90481-910a-4a41-9a55-14f7a2353caf" alt="Enhanced by Zemanta" /></a><span class="zem-script more-related pretty-attribution"><script src="http://static.zemanta.com/readside/loader.js" type="text/javascript"></script></span></div>
<p><a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/ho-scale/electric-train-ho/">Electric Train HO Scale &#8211; The Most Popular Choice</a> is a post from: <a href="http://trainsoscaledepot.com">Trains O Scale</a>:blog where you can get news on Trains O Scale and other model train collecting news.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
