<i>
<p>A commuter train leaves the station 4.0 hours after a freight train, with an average speed of 35 miles per hour faster than the freight train. They are on parallel tracks. Six hours after the commuter train leaves it catches up to the freight train. What is the average speed of the commuter train?
</p>
<p></i></p>
<p>(s + 35)t = (t +4)s<br />
st + 35t = st + 4s<br />
35t = 4s<br />
35t/4 = s<br />
35(6)/4 = s<br />
210/4 = s<br />
52.5 = s</p>
<p>Therefore, the commuter train has an average speed of 52.5 miles/hour</p>
