<i>
<p>My fiance and I are getting married on Saturday then flying to Vegas till Monday. We&#8217;re having trouble planning a few fun things to do while there &#8211; I&#8217;m 11 weeks pregnant so drinking is out. We bought tickets to see the Tournament of Kings at Excalibur on Sunday and are going to take a gondola ride at The Venetian as well. What else would be fun? We won&#8217;t have a car with us, and are staying at Trump Towers so we&#8217;re trying to stay on the strip. Any ideas for good food?
</p>
<p></i></p>
<p>Congratulations!  You must see Bellagio Fountain Show and the Conservatory in Bellagio.  The Mirage Volcano is very close to your Gondola at Venetien.  Jersey Boys is a great show at Palazzo/Venetien.  Prime Steakhouse at Bellagio is very romantic as well as Charlie Palmers at The Hotel at Mandalay Bay (close to your show on sunday.. but you will need reservations.) There&#8217;s a shark reef exhibition at Mandalay Bay as well.  I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;ll have fun even if you people watch.  The fashion show mall is a cool mall and  you can sit outside and sip on a Starbucks.<br />
Whatever you do, have fun and all the best.</p>
