<i>
<p>I am setting up a 30 gallon saltwater tank and I am looking at buy a skilter filter for it.  For a 30 gallon tank do I need a 250 gph skilter or 400gph skilter?<br />
Also, Do I need  seperate protien skimmer with this?
</p>
<p></i></p>
<p>I&#8217;m so glad to see some other reefers that know what they&#8217;re talking about.  Skilters are garbage.  Don&#8217;t waste your money.  It is so important to have quality equipment to SAVE money.  You&#8217;ll wind up trashing the Skilter and buying a better skimmer anyway.  So buy a better one up front.</p>
<p>A 30 gallon tank is not large.  You can easily get away with either the CPR AeroForce HOT (Hang On Tank) skimmer.  You can see the link below with a video of it in operation.  The AquaC Remora PRO is another decent skimmer for a 30g tank.</p>
<p>Once again, it&#8217;s better to buy the appropriate piece of equipment the first time than buying the same piece of equipment twice.</p>
<p>Best of luck,<br />
