<h2>Where Colorado Residents Can Apply For a Passport</h2>
<p>Colorado residents have numerous location available to them where they can apply for an United States passport. Passport offices, also known as passport application acceptance facilities are located in a lot of cities and towns throughout the state. The majority of these facilities are located in post offices or county government offices. Applicants for new passports are required to submit the application to an authorized agent.</p>
<p>At least one acceptance facility is located in each of the following counties: Adams, Alamosa, Arapahoe, Archuleta, Baca, Boulder, Broomfield, Chaffee, Cheyenne, Clear Creek, Crowley, Custer, Delta, Denver, Dolores, Douglas, Eagle, El Paso, Fremont, Garfield, Grand, Gunnison, Huerfano, Jackson, Jefferson, Kit Carson, La Plata, Lake, Larimer, Las Animas, Lincoln, Logan, Mesa, Moffat, Montezuma, Montrose, Morgan, Otero, Ouray, Phillips, Pitkin, Prowers, Pueblo, Rio Blanco, Rio Grande, Routt, Saguache, San Miguel, Summit, Teller, Washington, Weld, Yuma.</p>
<p>There are some counties that do not have a passport office. In this case, you need to look in a neighboring counties. El Paso county has the highest number of acceptance facilities with at least twelve. The state capital offers six location. Here is the address of a couple of these.</p>
<p>Denver County Court&nbsp;<br /> 1437 Bannock Street, Room 140&nbsp;<br /> Denver, Co 80204</p>
<p>USPO &#8211; Downtown Station&nbsp;<br /> 951 20th Street&nbsp;<br /> Denver, Co 80202-9998</p>
<p>You can choose either regular processing or expedited processing when you submit your application. You should receive your travel document in four to six weeks if you select regular processing. It should arrive in two to three weeks if you decide to expedite the process.</p>
<p>The State Department has regional agencies that attend travelers who need to obtain a passport in less than two weeks. If you are in an emergency situation and need to get your passport in less than two weeks, then you can apply at the Colorado passport agency located in Aurora. The address is as follows:</p>
<p>Colorado Passport Agency&nbsp;<br /> Cherry Creek III&nbsp;<br /> 3151 South Vaughn Way, Suite 600&nbsp;<br /> Aurora, CO 80014</p>
<p>You first schedule an appointment by calling 1-877-487-2778. Oftentimes, it takes many attempts before you are attended. Once the appointment is scheduled, you need to arrive at the Colorado agency with the completed but unsigned application Form DS-11 and the other required documents. You will also need two passport photos and payment for the fees. If all things are correct and in order, you should receive your new passport the same day.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>About the Author</strong><br />
</p>
<p>Visit U.S. Passport Service Guide to access a list of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.us-passport-service-guide.com/colorado-passport-acceptance-facility-list.html">Colorado passport offices</a>, download application forms and learn more about&nbsp;<a href="http://www.us-passport-service-guide.com/rush-passport-expediting.html">rush passport expediting</a>.</p>
