<i>
<p>It was made up of red plastic girders and beams with wall and roof panels and you could build bridges and skyscrapers with it. It came in a HUGE box with lots of compartments for all the parts, and I think it was re-issued in the late 80&#8242;s early 90&#8242;s under the same name from the 60&#8242;s. have been trying to remember the name because I would like to try and find one again! they were so much fun!<br />
Sorry guys, it was not an erector set. I believe it was made by Milton Bradly. with the wall and roof panels that snapped on to the girders it would make a quite realistic looking building.
</p>
<p></i></p>
<p>That was the girder and panel set and it was made by Kennor not Milton Bradley.  I had one and it was awesome.  I saw one of the bridge sets  on ebay for about  $20.00.  I think this was actually several different sets.  One was bridge related the other buildings.</p>
