<i>
<p>I have an O27 model train set running around my Christmas tree. I bought an NW2 switcher locomotive to pull freight cars around my Christmas tree? Is this incorrect or silly in historic terms to have a switcher as my locomotive pulling freight cars? I am just an amateur but just curious if a serious train enthusiast would turn their nose up at the idea?
</p>
<p></i></p>
<p>No it&#8217;s fine.We used to have many road switchers that used a switch engine to pull the cars.Now we mostly use older road power now but like i say it&#8217;s fine.Besides it&#8217;s your railroad&#8230;you can do anything you like on it!</p>
