<p>There is a movie from around late 70&#8242;s or early 80&#8242;s I need to know the title. It&#8217;s a kind of Romeo and Juliet story about two kids (she is a rich little girl from England, he is a poor boy from Venice) and it&#8217;s placed in Venice. All the movie, these two kids will try to pass under the &#8220;Kiss Bridge&#8221; in a gondola by sunset with the church&#8217;s bells tolling because the legend says that if they do this, they will be together forever. The finale is beatufil, &#8217;cause you see the girl in the back of her car and the boy running to catch her and jumping in the middle of the streets of Venice, screaming &#8220;I love you&#8221;. Please, if you can remember the title, HEEEELP!
