      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img style="margin-right:20px" src="http://trainsoscaledepot.com/wp-content/uploads/Milwaukee Road_5.jpg" alt="Milwaukee Road" border="0" align="left" /></p>
<h2>Avoiding Car Accidents: Keep Safe On The Road With These 4 Tips</h2>
<p>Nothing ruins a day, a year, or even a life more than a sudden car accident on America&#8217;s roads. And in this country, it is nearly impossible to live a functional life without constantly spending time behind the wheel of your car unless you live in some downtown area. So learning how to avoid car accidents before they happen is an essential skill in today&#8217;s environment, and while your friends might kid you a little bit for being an overly-defensive driver, nobody will be laughing when the worst happens.</p>
<p>So keep these four tips in mind to help avoid the worst case scenario altogether.</p>
<p>1. Look Into the Future</p>
<p>When I was younger, I often thought of car travel as a kind of time travelbecause things moved at such a fast pace, and you could look forward to see what waited for you ahead, as if looking into the future. Use this to your advantage, and always scan the road well ahead for any possible threats or obstacles. </p>
<p>Don&#8217;t just watch the road in front of you or the car just aheadscan your eyes over everything and watch the cars in front of the car ahead as well. Your eyes should be on the constant move, taking it all in, and when something does happen, you will be well prepared before you ever arrive.</p>
<p>2. Stick to the Right Shoulder</p>
<p>Do not be the type of driver who spends their entire day in the fast laneit is not only advisable to drive at the speed limit simply because going slower is safer but driving in the slow lane also gives you more options to get out of the road should something horrible happen. </p>
<p>When you are in the fast lane, you only have two real options to get out of the way, and that is by either pulling into the slow lane, where there are other cars, or even worse, pulling into oncoming traffic. Be sensible, and always think of the best way to respond to possible mishaps on the road.</p>
<p>3. Be More Cautious at Night</p>
<p>They say you should always adjust your driving to conditions, and in fact, that is the law. The same applies at night time when the lack of sunlight makes it harder to pay attention to what is going on in the road, especially further ahead in the distance. But there are other reasons night driving can be dangerous as well. </p>
<p>People out on the roads tend to be more reckless at nightsome feel that they can get away with more because they are under the cover of darkness. Others assume they will see the headlights of oncoming traffic even around blind corners, so they cut these closely. Some people get a bit of an adrenaline rush at night and feel a need to push the limits, and even worse, many drunk drivers take to the road at night. Even fatigue alone can be huge problemwhether it is you or other drivers. </p>
<p>At any rate, while night driving might seem ideal because there are less cars on the road, you must be much more aware of the people around you.</p>
<p>4. Be Judgmental</p>
<p>Most of us were told by our parents and teachers growing up that it is unfair to judge people and that you should resist the impulse to stereotype, but often, on the road, you need to give your instincts a little more breathing room. If you notice another car is pretty banged up and/or covered in healthy layer of dust, you might want to be on edge a little bit. Often, drivers who are careless about their car&#8217;s condition are also careless when behind the wheel. </p>
<p>Pay attention to driving behavior as welldrivers who stop suddenly, accelerate quickly, or do a lot of drifting around their lane. Whether these things suggest a drunk driver, a tired driver, or a careless driver, it is best to trust your first impressions when on the road.</p>
<p>Of course, we can&#8217;t avoid all car accidentssooner or later, most of us will have a fender bender, and hopefully we will avoid the worst kinds. Just practice defensive driving to do everything in your power to avoid an accident in the first place, and if something does happen, get on the phone immediately to contact a car accident attorney.</p>
